                    <ns0:app loc="line 3"><ns0:note>F lapis, interpreted by Amico, Castelli, Ferrara, Kirchhoff, Kaibel, Wessel as a &#947;, by Korhonen as a &#962;</ns0:note></ns0:app>
                    <ns0:app loc="line 3"><ns0:note>Kirchhoff, Kaibel: &#954;&#945;&#955;[&#945;&#957;]-; Korhonen: &#954;&#945;&#955;(&#945;&#957;)-</ns0:note></ns0:app>
                    <ns0:app loc="line 6"><ns0:note>Castelli: &#935;&#961;&#963;&#953;&#945;&#957;&#942; (sic); Kirchhoff: &#967;&#961;<ns0:corr>&#953;&#963;&#964;</ns0:corr>&#953;&#945;&#957;&#942;; Kaibel: &#967;&#961;&#951;&#962;<ns0:corr>&#964;</ns0:corr>&#953;&#945;&#957;&#942;; lapis, Korhonen: &#967;&#961;&#951;&#963;&#953;&#945;&#957;&#942; (see also Agnello 1953: 50 no.102 = <ns0:ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001655">ISic001655</ns0:ref>)</ns0:note></ns0:app>
